TO: BARBARA EPSTEIN

TL (XEROX), 1 p.

Switzerland





August 29th, 1971

Dear Barbara,

Your constant kindness in regard to my little grievances in the past encourages me to ask you to publish the short review which I enclose.1

A Mr. Rowe, Assistant Professor of Russian at New York University, who recently visited us at Montreux (and seemed to be a responsible and civilized person) has now exuded a book about me: I have nothing much to say about its first two parts, but its third part an